# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this React + Vite project following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics@^2.0.1` package using npm
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Generated `package-lock.json` to lock dependency versions

### 2. Code Changes
**Modified: `src/App.jsx`**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the main app container, just before the closing `</div>` tag
- Placement ensures analytics tracking is active across all pages of the application

### 3. Framework Compatibility
- Confirmed React + Vite framework from package.json and vite.config.js
- Followed React-specific implementation from official Vercel documentation
- No additional configuration required for React/Vite projects

## Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - New file with locked dependencies
- `src/App.jsx` - Added Analytics import and component
- `.gitignore` - Created to exclude build artifacts and node_modules

## Verification
✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✅ No build errors or warnings
✅ Analytics component properly integrated into React component tree
✅ All changes follow existing code patterns and structure

## Next Steps
To enable analytics tracking:
1. Deploy this project to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard for this project
3. Analytics data will start appearing after deployment

## Notes
- Analytics component is placed at the root level to track all pages
- The implementation is privacy-first and follows Vercel's best practices
- No environment variables or additional configuration required
- Analytics will only track data when deployed on Vercel platform
